overview: The user initiated a review of a recently developed interactive sleep
  questionnaire application. The core intent was to verify that the implemented
  database, API endpoints, and overall functionality align with the detailed
  acceptance criteria outlined in the provided project documentation. The
  application is designed to be a freemium tool, collecting minimal
  de-identified demographic data (year of birth, zipcode/county, sex). It guides
  patients through psychometrically validated questions to generate a narrative
  report. This report either points towards sleep health optimization guidance
  or provides probable diagnoses for specific sleep disorders (e.g., Insomnia,
  Sleep Apnea), offering recommendations for further information and clinical
  resources. The review process involved examining the questionnaire's
  structure, data models, API for response handling, CSV export, PDF report
  generation, and the admin dashboard for data access.
